<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I would like to change the timeout setting when connecting to an SMTP server and sending a mail. At the moment this is a constant in the Zend_Mail_Protocol_Abstract class:
const TIMEOUT_CONNECTION = 30;</p>

<p>Would be nice to have an option to change this, because 30 seconds is too much for a LAN connection, and switching to a backup SMTP takes at least 30 seconds with this setting, which is too much.</p>

